/*
:name: reserved_word_signal
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: top
:pyrope_top: top
*/

// Regression for 2i-issues F (now FIXED): cgen must escape SystemVerilog-2012
// reserved words used as signal names. `packed` is an IEEE-1800 keyword. cgen's
// get_scaped_name (inou/cgen/cgen_verilog.cpp) now escapes the full IEEE-1800
// keyword set, so it emits `\packed ` (escaped) instead of a bare `packed` that
// yosys (TOK_PACKED), iverilog -g2012, and verilator would reject.
//
// Purely combinational (no register) to isolate the cgen emission bug. The
// `:type: equiv` harness re-reads the GENERATED verilog through lgcheck/yosys, so
// this guards against a regression in the reserved-word escaping (the golden uses
// an escaped `\packed ` port; an adversarial sweep of 17 keywords — packed, bit,
// byte, int, shortint, longint, void, automatic, static, unique, priority,
// interface, modport, package, program, time, real — all verified escaped).
pub comb top(a:u8) -> (packed:u8) {
  packed = a + 1
}
